Otto Guenther v. Chicago Chronicle Company.Appeal from Circuit Court of Cook County.Wh. E. O’ÍSTeill, attorney for appellant.Daniel Y. Gallery, attorney for appellee.

1. Appellate Court Practice—Abstracts to Shoiv Exceptions.— The abstract must show the exceptions taken to the rulings of the court below.

This case was affirmed because no exception is shown by the abstract to have been taken to any ruling or judgment of the court, on the authority of Gibler v. City of Mattoon, 167 Ill. 18, and other cases.
